Amanda Khoza, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A KwaZulu-Natal man survived a shooting on Friday night, Netcare911 said on Saturday. Netcare911&rsquo;s Chris Botha said at around 22:07 paramedics responded to a shooting incident along Umhlatuzana Road in the Marianhill area of KZN. When they arrived at the scene the patient was brought on the back of a bakkie. Paramedics examined the man, who had sustained life-threatening gunshot wound.The man was stabilised at the scene transported to a Chatsworth hospital for further treatment. The exact details to the cause of the shooting is being investigated by the police, Botha said.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.